== Garlic Rice ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Lemony Green Beans ==

While rice cooks, trim @green beans{6%oz} if necessary. Toss on a #baking sheet with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== BBQ-Rubbed Pork Chops ==

Meanwhile, pat @pork chops{12%oz} dry with #paper towels. Season all over with @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. (Lower heat if pork begins to brown too quickly.)

Turn off heat; transfer pork to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Return same pan to medium-high heat. Stir in @peach jam{1%unit}, @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings), and juice from half the lemon. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Return pork to pan and turn a few times to coat.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and season with salt and pepper. Toss green beans with lemon zest.

Divide rice, green beans, and pork between plates. Spoon any remaining sauce from pan over pork. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.